South Africa  and Ghana are in talks
for PetroSA to buy a stake in  Ghana National Petroleum Corp. ,
state-owned South Africa Broadcasting Corp. reported, citing
South Africaâ€™s deputy president  Kgalema Motlanthe .  The final agreement is expected in a month, the
Johannesburg-based public broadcaster said in a  report  on its
website. The agreement will provide security of supply for South
Africa, it quoted Motlanthe as saying.  As part of the deal, South Africa has agreed to assist
Ghana to develop the Akosombo hydro power station, according to
the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
